    "Such subtleties plague other graphene-based moiré materials, but are less problematic for some other systems 20.",
    "Below, we list some commonly used interaction schemes for TBG by specifying the reference density matrix in the BM band basis.• Full average scheme: This corresponds to ρ 0 τ s;ab = 1 2 δ ab for all bands.",
    "This is typically utilized in many-body calculations that work in the plane wave basis and retain all BM bands (i.e.",
    "no band projection).• Central average scheme: This corresponds to ρ 0 τ s;ab = 1 2 δ ab for the central bands and ρ 0 τ s;ab = δ ab for the remote valence bands.",
    "The remote conduction bands are unoccupied in the reference state."
  ],
